e>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cw>filiae\u003C/w>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text according to ILipara 767\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#DEE\">\n                \u003Cp>Hilara (set this up) to her daughter.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"it\" resp=\"#DEE\">\n                \u003Cp>Hilara (ha predisposto questo) per la sua figlia.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>It is also possible to imagine that final E has been dropped from Hilara and so 'filiae' is descriptive of Hilara instead, implicitly erected by her parent(s).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"ILipara\">\n \u2028                        \u003Cauthor>Bernabó-Brea\u003C/author>\n \u2028                        \u003Cauthor>Cavalier\u003C/author>\n \u2028                        \u003Cauthor>Campagna\u003C/author>\n \u2028                        \u003Cdate>2003\u003C/date> \n                        \u003CcitedRange>767\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/VDAQH5D2\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000541\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000541\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl/>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
